<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="118" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1545,2040]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1653,1679]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is superficially is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2008" box="[788,891,1654,1680]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kareni">
<emphasis box="[788,891,1654,1680]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">B. kareni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[906,972,1654,1680]" captionStart="FIGURES 1-8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1792,1816]" captionTargetBox="[177,1422,239,1749]" captionTargetId="figure-24@2.[151,1435,181,1768]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1-8. Bellulia spp., adults. 1. B. kareni (after Fibiger 2008); 2. B. tenebrosa sp. n., holotype, Cambodia; 3. B. clara sp. n., holotype, Cambodia; 4. B. mariannae (after Fibiger 2008); 5. B. parabella (after Fibiger 2008); 6. B. hanae (after Fibiger 2008); 7. B. jiaxuanae sp. n., holotype, China; 8. B. bibella (after Fibiger et al. 2011)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4561449" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4561449/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
), but can be distinguish by the following characters: the forewing is rather broad (much narrover in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2008" box="[794,894,1690,1716]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kareni">
<emphasis box="[794,894,1690,1716]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">B. kareni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); the basal line is distinct (in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2008" box="[1217,1318,1690,1716]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kareni">
<emphasis box="[1217,1318,1690,1716]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">B. kareni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it presents only on the costal margin); the antemedial line is broad and waved (in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2008" box="[944,1046,1726,1752]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kareni">
<emphasis box="[944,1046,1726,1752]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">B. kareni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is smoothly curved); postmedial line bears big costal marks (in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2008" box="[489,590,1762,1788]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kareni">
<emphasis box="[489,590,1762,1788]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">B. kareni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with small costal blackish-brown mark); subterminal line broad, with grains (in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2008" box="[191,294,1798,1824]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kareni">
<emphasis box="[191,294,1798,1824]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">B. kareni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is thin and smooth); the hindwing is less darker than forewing (in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2008" box="[1079,1183,1798,1824]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kareni">
<emphasis box="[1079,1183,1798,1824]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">B. kareni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ratherit is lighter than forewing, with weakly metallic luster). In the male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Han &amp; Kononenko" authorityYear="2021" box="[874,1016,1834,1860]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenebrosa">
<emphasis box="[874,1016,1834,1860]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">B. tenebrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1033,1116,1834,1860]" captionStart="FIGURES 17-22" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1811,1835]" captionTargetBox="[167,1416,230,1769]" captionTargetId="figure-31@8.[151,1435,201,1788]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 17-22. Bellulia spp., male genitalia. 17. B. kareni (after Fibiger 2008); 18. B. tenebrosa sp. n., holotype, Cambodia, genit. prep. hhl-3720-1; 19. B. clara sp. n., holotype, Cambodia, genit. prep. hhl-3728-1; 20. B. parabella (after Fibiger 2008); 21. B. hanae (after Fibiger 2008); 22. B. jiaxuanae sp. n., holotype, China, genit. prep. hhl-3537-1." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4561455" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4561455/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
) the tegumen much broader than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2008" box="[238,340,1870,1896]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kareni">
<emphasis box="[238,340,1870,1896]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">B. kareni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the ventral part of the tegumen is fused to the fultura superior bearing a prominent, log-like processes on each side which are thinner than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2008" box="[661,763,1906,1932]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kareni">
<emphasis box="[661,763,1906,1932]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">B. kareni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[778,861,1906,1932]" captionStart="FIGURES 17-22" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1811,1835]" captionTargetBox="[167,1416,230,1769]" captionTargetId="figure-31@8.[151,1435,201,1788]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 17-22. Bellulia spp., male genitalia. 17. B. kareni (after Fibiger 2008); 18. B. tenebrosa sp. n., holotype, Cambodia, genit. prep. hhl-3720-1; 19. B. clara sp. n., holotype, Cambodia, genit. prep. hhl-3728-1; 20. B. parabella (after Fibiger 2008); 21. B. hanae (after Fibiger 2008); 22. B. jiaxuanae sp. n., holotype, China, genit. prep. hhl-3537-1." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4561455" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4561455/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
); in the right valva the process of costa is short and straight, cone-shaped, protrudes from the exterior half of the costa (in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2008" box="[952,1055,1942,1968]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kareni">
<emphasis box="[952,1055,1942,1968]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">B. kareni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is horn-shaped, protrudes from the medial part of the costa); the sacculus is apically rounded (in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2008" box="[899,1002,1978,2004]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kareni">
<emphasis box="[899,1002,1978,2004]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">B. kareni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is a narrow liguliform process); the aedeagus narrower than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2008" box="[453,555,2014,2040]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kareni">
<emphasis box="[453,555,2014,2040]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">B. kareni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Han &amp; Kononenko" authorityYear="2021" box="[609,699,2014,2040]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clara">
<emphasis box="[609,699,2014,2040]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">B. clara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[714,798,2014,2040]" captionStart="FIGURES 17-22" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1811,1835]" captionTargetBox="[167,1416,230,1769]" captionTargetId="figure-31@8.[151,1435,201,1788]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 17-22. Bellulia spp., male genitalia. 17. B. kareni (after Fibiger 2008); 18. B. tenebrosa sp. n., holotype, Cambodia, genit. prep. hhl-3720-1; 19. B. clara sp. n., holotype, Cambodia, genit. prep. hhl-3728-1; 20. B. parabella (after Fibiger 2008); 21. B. hanae (after Fibiger 2008); 22. B. jiaxuanae sp. n., holotype, China, genit. prep. hhl-3537-1." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4561455" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4561455/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
